  "notes": [
    "The game does not use a simple 'Daze' or 'Incapacitate' named effect - these are implemented through the suppression state machine and skill disabling handlers.",
    "Visual stun and logical stun are separate - visual stun affects animations while logical stun affects gameplay mechanics.",
    "Suppression is the primary daze mechanism - State 2 (PinnedDown) effectively incapacitates the actor unless they have UsableWhenPinnedDown skills.",
    "Commanders are immune to the Panicked morale state, providing resilience against morale-based incapacitation.",
    "The InterceptAPChangeHandler provides a mechanism for skills to modify or negate AP reduction effects."
  ]
